  "read": "The compact-return contract is correct in the 512-row smoke and gives a real but modest tail improvement: at max current-best tail rows it is 33.175 ms versus 34.950 ms for scatter-inclusive grouped-MM and 36.422 ms padded VJP. This recovers about 1.78 ms from the return/scatter boundary, but remains 5.49 ms slower than grouped-MM-only at the same tail. Therefore the next implementation still needs a fused/batched compact helper VJP plus compact dispatcher return; compact return alone is not enough to close the MoE/EP wall.",
